title: For Sale:  Custom Build AR15 5.56/.223
postcontent:
I have an AR15 that I built from the ground up using the best parts available to its purpose, this could be a scary proposition except that I work with my hands everyday, and am Very knowledgeable on building firearms. This Rifle is chambered in 5.56/.223 The Lower shown in the photo is not the Noveske lower is has now.

Upper Assembly:
Rainier Arms "Made by Mega" Upper w/ shell deflector, dust cover, but No Forward Assist, this upper is rare and no longer available anywhere.
Spike's Pirate ARRGH dust cover
Dehorned custom BCM Gunfighter Medium length Latch Charge Handle
Primary Weapon Systems Billet Isonite Coated FA style Low Drag Bolt Carrier
Lewis Machine & Tool Enhanced 5.56 Supported Chamber Dual Extractor Spring Bolt Headspace Verified
16" Noveske Recon Mid-Length Improved Polygonal 5 groove Rifling, 1 in 7" twist Matching Noveske Lo Pro Gas block and Midlength Gas Tube
Noveske 13.5" NSR Key Mod Hand Guard
1 NSR short rail
1 nsr medium rail
1 nsr qd attachment point
Vortex Fluted Flash Eliminator
Aimpoint Comp M4 High Battery Location US Army Red Dot 2 MOA, 80,000hrs on 1 AA
L3 Eotech G23 Tan 3x Magnifier w/ 2nd Generation FTS QD mount

Lower Assembly:
Noveske Billet Gen 2 N4 Flared Magazine Well Lower Receiver
Geiselle Super Dynamic Combat 3.75lb total pull 2 stage flat trigger group
KNS Gen 2 Anti rotating sear/hammer pin set FA rated
Magpul UBR adjustable presets, Toughest Length adjustable stock made, Completely shrouds the buffer tube with a tough aluminum sleeve as well as impact polymer.
Aluminum Strike plate for UBR stock "glass,door, and face breaching"
Magpul MOE-K reduced grip angle pistol grip "so you can run the stock comfortably at a short length of pull for cqb"
H Buffer, allows perfect function with .223 as well as 5.56 Nato spec ammo
CS Extra Power Flat Wire Buffer Spring "round wire springs bind while the flat wire stack perfectly, no spring noise with this rifle.
60 degree short throw Ambi noveske/magpul safety lever
1 New in package Lancer Advanced Warfighter 30rd Magazine "Clear Smoke color"

The Upper, Lower, charge handle, handguard have all been professionally cerakoted Magpul Flat Dark Earth, in addition the magnifier, the stock, and the pistol grip are all Flat Dark Earth.
I have over $4,000 in this build, it has exactly 260 rounds fired through it "it Loves 69-77gr sierra matchkings, properly loaded will produce 1/4" groups hot or cold @ 100 yards.

When I broke in this rifle, I removed the gas block/tube and hand guard, and used break in loads w/ guilding metal jackets loaded over 80% case filled with IMR Trail Boss Powder, for the first 20 rounds I cleaned the bore of all copper and carbon fowling between every shot, for the next 20 rounds i did the same as a redundancy as there was no more copper building up in the bore. The result is a barrel that needs fowling removed very rarely, and during breakin the barrel never got warm, This gun shoots the same point of aim, the same groups, hot or cold. I built this rifle to be a short to mid range combat ready rifle. the action is so smooth you have to feel it to beleive it, after the lube burns off it stays slicker than melting ice. This rifle weighs 10lbs but the balance makes it feel very nice and effortless to shoulder the weapon. Also at night with 5.56 loads there s such a low muzzle signature and the kill flash on the aim point won't give away your position cause it eliminates optic reflection

The Price is Non Negotiable, and I am not interested in Trades at this time, The STI 1911 and theBenchmade knife is not included. However I may be interested in a nice FN Scar+

title: For Sale:  NC Laws for private sales...Incase you didnt know
location: NC Laws for private sales, So You Know, Jacksonville, North Carolina
postcontent:
Protect yourself, know your State/Federal Laws.

First, there is no Federal law what so ever on private sales of firearms in state regardless if its a long-gun or handgun, you do however have to follow your local and state laws. And if the sale is between state lines it must go through an FFL.

Both Party's In NC:
North Carolina Law does not require a private sale of a Handgun nor a Long-gun to be "Transferred" through an FFL. All that is required in NC is that the Seller collect a Pistol Purchasing Permit from the Buyer OR the Buyer must have a Valid NC Concealed Carry License if buying a handgun. If you would like to copy the license for your records that's fine but it is not required. Also a bill of sale is a good idea for any future problems, but is not required. The above is applicable whether Military or a Civilian.

One Party Out of State:
If you are in NC and they are in lets say SC, if you are the buyer, you must have it sent to an FFL because the firearm is crossing state lines from another state, this is a Federal Law. If your the Seller you can do it two ways:
A) Personally mail your handgun/long-gun via UPS or FEDEX 2-Day Air to the buyers FFL of choice. You must go to a FED-x or UPS facility, not a mailing center.
B)Take your weapon to your local FFL and have them mail it to the Buyers FFL, but you will have to pay a bullshit transfer fee for them to transfer it to the Buyers FFL even though all that is involved is recording your name, number and gun info in a book. The only benefit to doing it this way is now its a Business dealing with a Business so its a little harder for you to get ripped off.

The above is NC State law. Anything that a seller or buyer does beyond this is there choice. If you want to do a private sale through and FFL then that's fine, but its not required and your wasting money.

The ADCOR B.E.A.R. is currently in the new US Military Individual Carbine trials for the new AR platform that will be replacing/upgrading the M4, along with the FN MK16 SCAR-L, Remington ACR, Colt APC, and the Heckler and Koch HK416.

Following this, the B.E.A.R. was able to shoot a .88 MOA group at 100 yards with 69-grain match ammo.

B.E.A.R. (Brown Enhanced Automatic Rifle) models from Adcor Defense feature a patent-bearing, gas piston system with a free-floating barrel for increased accuracy. This is due to the piston's incorporation into the upper half of the forward rail system - so it never touches the barrel. Extremely close machine tolerances eliminate the need for piston rings. With a tool-less field strip design, a B.E.A.R. requires nothing more than a firing pin to disassemble, yet remains strong. The piston's cyclical rate for a controlled rate of fire adjusts with a turn of the gas plug located in the front piston assembly. Because diminished heat reaches the upper, hot gases and carbon particulates are prevented from entering the receiver, lubricant lasts longer and maintenance is simplified. Due to superior design, the B.E.A.R. has no carrier tilt and low fouling of the chamber and action.

title: For Sale/Trade:  Sig Sauer p-250 three cal pack 9mm, 40, 45 night sights extra mag & trigger
postcontent:
If you are looking for a Sig reliability and don't know which caliber to choose, then why choose? Have the pistol in three calibers or more upon your choice. The P-250 versatility lets this one pistol convert to 4 different calibers. I am including the pistol in the most popular of calibers. The 9 mm, the .40 cal and the .45, but you can add on the .357 sig if desired by purchasing the caliber X-change kit. The pistol operates in Double Action Only ( DAO) 

The configurations I am selling include: the 9mm full size with night sights and one 17 rd. magazine,  The .40 cal compact with night sights and 2- 14 round magazines, and the .45 with plain sights and 2- 10 round magazines. One metal frame with trigger group.( the serialized part--"the gun") There is also a short trigger, sig box, and one plastic case.

The way Sig designed the pistol it can be set up in 12 different configurations- Subcompact, Compact, and Full size in four different calibers just by purchasing the caliber exchange kits through the mail. Unlike a Glock, if the frame is damaged, you do not need to send back the frame. Simply order a new one for $48. The trigger group can be removed and put into any P-250 frame.

Check out the specs and additional pictures on this gun at: http://www.sigsauer.com/CatalogProductList/pistols-p250.aspx

Here is a Guns and Ammo magazine review:  http://www.gunsandammo.com/reviews/one-serious-sig-sig-p250-review/

You can youtube the video of the caliber exchange feature: http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=gJcRbOztrrw

The retail for this package is : Complete gun with trigger group and night sights is $642, the 2 caliber exchange kits are $299 each the night sights $72, the extra mags are about  $40 each. The extra trigger is $35. for a total retail of $1427. Yes this is used so I would take about $975. It is well cared for. This is the second generation sig with the EAK serial number prefix. Because of its growing popularity, The exchange kits are back ordered everywhere.  But you can have it all now. 

http://www.topgunsupply.com/p250-caliber-x-change-kits/

Like many of our products, the MRDS is designed to not only meet but exceed military durability specifications for equipment used by special operations personnel under extreme combat conditions. The lens of the MRDS is made from a lightweight, impact resistant polymer with an anti-reflective coating. Its rugged housing is molded from advanced polymers reducing weight without sacrificing operational durability.

The MRDS has been waterproofed to 66 feet for 2 hours, frozen in ice, drop tested, subjected to a 48-hour salt fog, tested to withstand vibration, submitted to extreme temperature shock and shot on a variety of firearms for thousands of rounds. It has an operational temperature range of -40o C to 49o C and passes the MIL-STD 810G environmental testing protocols.

Powered by a single 1632 battery that allows the unit to operate up to 1-year in Auto mode, the MRDS weighs just 0.85 ounces including battery. The top-load battery compartment design means no loss of zero when changing the battery.
